{"title":"Bianchi’s New Aquila RC—A Time Trial Missile Built for Pure Speed","link":"https://bikerumor.com/bianchi-new-aquila-rc-tt-bike/","date":1738855833000,"content":"<p><img src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Bianchi-Aquila-RC-full-bike-.png\" width=\"754\" height=\"626\" alt=\"Bianchi Aquila RC full bike\" /></p>\n<p>Bianchi just dropped its latest TT speed machine, the Aquila RC. They didn’t just tweak a few tubes and call it a day. This bike results from 20 months of relentless R&amp;D, with one goal: make the fastest TT bike possible. Meet the all-new Bianchi New Aquila RC.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Bianchi-Aquila-RC-headon.png\"><img width=\"838\" height=\"640\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Bianchi-Aquila-RC-headon.png\" alt=\"Bianchi Aquila RC headon\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Bianchi-Aquila-RC-headon.png 838w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Bianchi-Aquila-RC-headon-297x227.png 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Bianchi-Aquila-RC-headon-120x92.png 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Bianchi-Aquila-RC-headon-768x587.png 768w\" /></a><figcaption>All Photos: Bianchi </figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Aquila RC makes its racing debut this Sunday at the Étoile des Bessèges. A race where every watt saved can mean the difference between a podium and a near-miss.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Bianchi-Aquila-RC-drawing-.png\"><img width=\"1090\" height=\"816\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Bianchi-Aquila-RC-drawing-.png\" alt=\"Bianchi Aquila RC drawing\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Bianchi-Aquila-RC-drawing-.png 1090w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Bianchi-Aquila-RC-drawing--297x222.png 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Bianchi-Aquila-RC-drawing--120x90.png 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Bianchi-Aquila-RC-drawing--768x575.png 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>Fast Isn’t an Afterthought—It’s the Philosophy</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Bianchi’s Reparto Corse division took the same holistic design approach used to develop the Oltre RC Hyperbike. Treating the rider and bike as a single aerodynamic system. That means every tube, every component, and every millimeter of rider position has been optimized, tested, and refined. Over and over again.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Bianchi-Aquila-RC-seat-.png\"><img width=\"996\" height=\"754\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Bianchi-Aquila-RC-seat-.png\" alt=\"Bianchi Aquila RC seat\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Bianchi-Aquila-RC-seat-.png 996w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Bianchi-Aquila-RC-seat--297x225.png 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Bianchi-Aquila-RC-seat--120x91.png 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Bianchi-Aquila-RC-seat--768x581.png 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Bianchi-Aquila-RC-rear-.png\"><img width=\"1002\" height=\"892\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Bianchi-Aquila-RC-rear-.png\" alt=\"Bianchi Aquila RC rear\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Bianchi-Aquila-RC-rear-.png 1002w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Bianchi-Aquila-RC-rear--297x264.png 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Bianchi-Aquila-RC-rear--120x107.png 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Bianchi-Aquila-RC-rear--768x684.png 768w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The name Aquila has long been part of Bianchi’s identity—it means<em> “eagle,</em>” symbolizing power, speed, and precision. The new Aquila RC embodies that more than ever, bringing next-level aerodynamics, aggressive positioning, and real-world speed gains.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Bianchi-Aquila-RC.png\"><img width=\"952\" height=\"572\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Bianchi-Aquila-RC.png\" alt=\"Bianchi Aquila RC\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Bianchi-Aquila-RC.png 952w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Bianchi-Aquila-RC-297x178.png 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Bianchi-Aquila-RC-120x72.png 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Bianchi-Aquila-RC-768x461.png 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>TT Optimization—Down to the Watt</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Bianchi worked with WorldTour TT specialists and Arkéa-B&amp;B Hotels’ Kévin Vauquelin (Tour de France stage winner and Paris 2024 Olympian) to fine-tune every detail. The result? A bike that’s not just fast in the tunnel—it’s fast where it matters.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Bianchi-Aquila-RC-sticks-.png\"><img width=\"978\" height=\"888\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Bianchi-Aquila-RC-sticks-.png\" alt=\"Bianchi Aquila RC sticks\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Bianchi-Aquila-RC-sticks-.png 978w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Bianchi-Aquila-RC-sticks--297x270.png 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Bianchi-Aquila-RC-sticks--120x109.png 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Bianchi-Aquila-RC-sticks--768x697.png 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Bianchi-Aquila-RC-bars-.png\"><img width=\"986\" height=\"652\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Bianchi-Aquila-RC-bars-.png\" alt=\"Bianchi Aquila RC bars\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Bianchi-Aquila-RC-bars-.png 986w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Bianchi-Aquila-RC-bars--297x196.png 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Bianchi-Aquila-RC-bars--120x79.png 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Bianchi-Aquila-RC-bars--768x508.png 768w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Some key design choices:</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>77.5° Seat Tube Angle</strong> – Dialed to match the preferences of WorldTour TT pros, allowing for a more aggressive, aerodynamic position.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Refined Tube Shapes </strong>– Engineered to leverage the “sailing effect”, turning side winds into forward thrust.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Cockpit Collaboration with Vision FSA </strong>– Fully integrated, adjustable, and built for pure aero efficiency.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Bianchi-Aquila-RC-full-bike-side-.png\"><img width=\"740\" height=\"594\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Bianchi-Aquila-RC-full-bike-side-.png\" alt=\"Bianchi Aquila RC full bike side\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Bianchi-Aquila-RC-full-bike-side-.png 740w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Bianchi-Aquila-RC-full-bike-side--297x238.png 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Bianchi-Aquila-RC-full-bike-side--120x96.png 120w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>Speed Gains You Can Measure</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Here’s where it gets real. The new Aquila RC saves 16.1 watts at 50 km/h (31 mph) compared to its predecessor, over a 40.7 km time trial, translating to a 37-second advantage—a difference that can decide the podium.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Bianchi-Aquila-RC-close-up-legs-.png\"><img width=\"1038\" height=\"864\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Bianchi-Aquila-RC-close-up-legs-.png\" alt=\"Bianchi Aquila RC close up legs\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Bianchi-Aquila-RC-close-up-legs-.png 1038w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Bianchi-Aquila-RC-close-up-legs--297x247.png 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Bianchi-Aquila-RC-close-up-legs--120x100.png 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Bianchi-Aquila-RC-close-up-legs--768x639.png 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Bianchi-Aquila-RC-management-.png\"><img width=\"938\" height=\"736\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Bianchi-Aquila-RC-management-.png\" alt=\"Bianchi Aquila RC management\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Bianchi-Aquila-RC-management-.png 938w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Bianchi-Aquila-RC-management--297x233.png 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Bianchi-Aquila-RC-management--120x94.png 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Bianchi-Aquila-RC-management--768x603.png 768w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong><em>How did they get there?</em></strong> Bianchi’s Reparto Corse didn’t just rely on CFD and wind tunnel testing. They went all-in with real-world rider testing and some mannequin testing. Even developing an innovative artificial leg movement tool to measure how human motion interacts with aerodynamics. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Bianchi-Aquila-RC-logo.png\"><img width=\"758\" height=\"622\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Bianchi-Aquila-RC-logo.png\" alt=\"Bianchi Aquila RC logo\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Bianchi-Aquila-RC-logo.png 758w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Bianchi-Aquila-RC-logo-297x244.png 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Bianchi-Aquila-RC-logo-120x98.png 120w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The bike was tested in multiple configurations: static, with moving legs, and with different fork designs. Ensuring it’s optimized for the real demands of racing.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Bianchi-Aquila-RC-full-bike-.png\"><img width=\"754\" height=\"626\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Bianchi-Aquila-RC-full-bike-.png\" alt=\"Bianchi Aquila RC full bike\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Bianchi-Aquila-RC-full-bike-.png 754w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Bianchi-Aquila-RC-full-bike--297x247.png 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Bianchi-Aquila-RC-full-bike--120x100.png 120w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>Frame, Fit &amp; Availability</h3>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>Frameset Weight: 1.3 kg (Size M), Fork: 400 g</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Sizes: S, M, L</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Max Tire Clearance: 28 mm</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Colorway: Glossy Black &amp; Metallic Celeste with Celeste CK16 accents</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Retail Price: €5,449 (Frameset Only)</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h3>Race Debut</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The Aquila RC hits the pro circuit this Sunday, with Arkéa-B&amp;B Hotels racing it at the final stage of Étoile des Bessèges. </p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.bianchi.com/bikes/bikes/road/tt-triathlon-road/aquila-rc/\">Bianchi.com </a></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/bianchi-new-aquila-rc-tt-bike/\">Bianchi’s New Aquila RC—A Time Trial Missile Built for Pure Speed</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Jordan Villella","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"e21a78adddb4bb97280faadce300044e059c1d9c45b9c8cd2b9ebe2ee8a98d93","category":"Cycling"}